                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" fkcefr="a1" hclass="sense" id="adverb_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a word that adds more information about place, time, manner, cause or degree to a verb, an adjective, a phrase or another adverb</span></span><ul class="examples" htag="ul" hclass="examples"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">In ‘speak kindly’, ‘incredibly deep’, ‘just in time’ and ‘too quickly’, ‘kindly’, ‘incredibly’, ‘just’ and ‘too’ are all adverbs.</span></li></ul> <span class="xrefs" hclass="xrefs" htag="span" xt="see"><span class="prefix">see also</span> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sentence-adverb" title="sentence adverb definition"><span class="xr-g" href="sentenceadverb_e" bord="n" dict="all"><span class="xh">sentence adverb</span></span></a></span><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/language?level=a1" title="Topic language"><span class="topic" href="l2:communication:language?cefr=a1"><span class="topic_name">Language</span><span class="topic_cefr">a1</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="snippet" id="adverb_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class="body"><span class="unbox">adjective</span><ul class="collocs_list"><li class="li">interrogative</li><li class="li">sentence</li></ul><span class="unbox">adverb</span><ul class="collocs_list"><li class="li">modify something</li><li class="li">qualify something</li></ul><span class="unbox">phrases</span><ul class="collocs_list"><li class="li">an adverb of degree</li><li class="li">an adverb of manner</li><li class="li">an adverb of place</li><li class="li">…</li></ul><span class="xref_to_full_entry">See <a class="Ref" href="